            "content": "## Summary\n\nRelocate the AI SDK / LangGraph agent loop out of `apps/web/lib/ai` into the `apps/api` **worker**, so the HTTP/render path does no agent work (the SPEC §9.5 boundary).\n\n## Context\n\nSPEC.md §9.5, §23.1; see the AGENTS.md gotcha. Today the LangGraph supervisor / ReAct loop runs inside `apps/web`; it must execute in the worker that processes runs (#48). This is the migration the durable-run design assumes.\n\n## Design\n\n- Move the agent graph + provider wiring (`@langchain/*`, `ai`) into the `apps/api` worker.\n- The worker invokes the graph within a run; the graph emits `run_events` (model deltas, tool calls) through the pipeline (#48).\n- `apps/web` calls only the run API (POST message → `run_id`; subscribe via #49). Remove agent execution from web request handlers.\n- Keep server-side provider packages in the worker; `apps/web` retains only the client-side AI SDK (`@ai-sdk/react`).\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] the agent graph executes in the worker, not in any web request handler\n- [ ] `apps/web` interacts only through the run API + SSE\n- [ ] existing chat behaviour is preserved end-to-end\n\n## Requirements\n\n- #48 — durable run pipeline (the worker the agent loop moves into)\n",
