            "content": "## v0.2: Durable runs\n\nThe durability upgrade over v0.1's direct streaming: every message becomes a worker-processed run with an append-only event stream, so progress survives a refresh and longer / tool-using runs become possible.\n\n### Architecture overview\n\npg-boss queue on Postgres (#47) → the API only stores + enqueues while a worker appends to the run-event store (#48) → clients replay events over SSE and survive refresh (#49) → the v0.1 single-model loop moves into that worker (#50). Durable state lives in Postgres; the worker is the executor. Postgres-first — no Redis/broker (SPEC §24.0).\n\n### Key design decisions\n\n- The API thread does no model work — validate / store / enqueue / return (SPEC §9.5).\n- The run-event store is append-only and cursor-replayable; the UI subscribes, never holds state.\n- Queue + scheduler are pg-boss on Postgres, behind a swappable interface (SPEC §23.4, §24.0–§24.0.1).\n\n### Layer 1: Foundation\n\n- [ ] #47 — pg-boss queue + scheduler on Postgres\n\n### Layer 2: Pipeline\n\n- [ ] #48 — durable run pipeline (message → run → worker → event store) (requires #47)\n\n### Layer 3: Surface & migration\n\n- [ ] #49 — refresh-safe SSE run-event replay (requires #48)\n- [ ] #50 — move the single-model loop into the worker (requires #48)\n\n### Dependency graph\n\n```mermaid\nflowchart TD\n    Q47[\"#47 pg-boss queue\"]\n    P48[\"#48 run pipeline\"]\n    S49[\"#49 SSE replay\"]\n    M50[\"#50 loop → worker\"]\n\n    Q47 --> P48\n    P48 --> S49\n    P48 --> M50\n```\n\n### Success criteria\n\n- A message creates a durable run processed by a worker, not the HTTP thread.\n- Refreshing mid-run restores progress from persisted events.\n- The v0.1 single-model loop runs in the worker; `apps/web` only calls the run API.\n",
